        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the dough and chill",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Cream the butter and sugar until pale. Beat in the egg yolk. Add the mixed spice and lemon zest. Sift over the flour and mix to a dough, adding the currants and enough milk to bring everything together. Flatten into a disc, wrap, and refrigerate for 20 minutes.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Roll, cut, and bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 180°C conventional. Line two baking trays with baking paper. Roll the dough on a lightly floured surface to 7 to 8 mm thick. Cut with a 7 cm fluted round cutter, re-rolling the scraps. Place on the trays. Bake for 12 minutes, then brush quickly with beaten egg white and dust generously with caster sugar. Return to the oven for 3 more minutes until pale gold and the sugar glaze is just set. Leave on the tray for 5 minutes before moving to a rack.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
